he discussion is relevant to the unrestricted set of languages, some of the assumptions made in the implementation restrict the useful application of the algorithms to languages in which the average number of affixes per word is less than what is found in such languages as Finnish, Hungarian, and Swahili, and we restrict our testing in the present report to more widely studied European languages.
    Our general goal, however, is the treatment of unrestricted natural languages.
